    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="section faq-section" id="faq">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header">
                <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <p class="section-subtitle">Everything you need to know</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-grid">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <span class="faq-icon">❓</span>
                        <h4>Does it work with self-hosted JIRA?</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes! BugWizard AI supports both JIRA Cloud and self-hosted JIRA Server/Data Center. Just enter your instance URL and API token in settings.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <span class="faq-icon">🔐</span>
                        <h4>Is my PAT/API token safe?</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Absolutely. Your credentials are stored only in your browser's localStorage — never sent to any BugWizard server. All API calls go directly from your browser to Azure DevOps or JIRA. We have zero access to your tokens.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <span class="faq-icon">🔑</span>
                        <h4>Can I use my own AI API key?</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes! BugWizard supports 10 AI providers. Bring your own OpenAI, Claude, Gemini, Groq, or any other supported API key. You can also use free tiers from providers like Groq and OpenRouter.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <span class="faq-icon">💰</span>
                        <h4>What's included in the free trial?</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Everything. Full access to all features including AI Bug Creator, Retest Automator, Ozzy AI, Video Compressor, and all 10 AI providers. No credit card required. No feature limits.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <span class="faq-icon">🏢</span>
                        <h4>Do you offer team/enterprise plans?</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Coming soon! We're working on team features including shared templates, team dashboards, and admin controls. Join the waitlist to get early access and special pricing.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <span class="faq-icon">🌐</span>
                        <h4>Does it work offline?</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Partially. BugWizard is a PWA that caches core functionality. You can draft bugs offline, but pushing to Azure DevOps or JIRA requires an internet connection.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

